# gen38: longer context via trigram backoff. The decode loop now conditions on
# the previous TWO words (cont2), backing off to the bigram when the 2-word
# context is unseen. This lets the same middle word continue differently
# depending on what came before it -- conditioning on more of the running
# output, the way an LLM does. Frequency choice is reused. Held-out tokens.
> learn sequence: red apple pie
< Learned 2 transition(s).
> learn sequence: green apple juice
< Learned 2 transition(s).
# "apple" is ambiguous as a bigram, but the trigram context decides:
> say red
< red apple pie
> say green
< green apple juice
# No 2-word context (single seed) -> back off to the bigram model.
> say apple
< apple pie